[I] Scheme compiler

[T] Chez Scheme is both a programming language and an implementation of that
[T] language, with supporting tools and documentation.
[T]
[T] As a superset of the language described in the Revised6 Report on the
[T] Algorithmic Language Scheme (R6RS), Chez Scheme supports all standard
[T] features of Scheme, including first-class procedures, proper treatment of
[T] tail calls, continuations, user-defined records, libraries, exceptions,
[T] and hygienic macro expansion.

[U] https://www.scheme.com/

[A] Cisco Systems, Inc.
[M] Tomas Glozar <tglozar@gmail.com>

[C] base/development
[F] NO-LTO.gcc

[L] APL
[V] 10.4.1
[P] X -----5---9 500.000

[CV-URL] https://github.com/cisco/ChezScheme/releases
[D] 31195af656cd5ed2e7a534a7db6803d651a37d47d3929f48e03372b1 csv10.4.1.tar.gz https://github.com/cisco/ChezScheme/releases/download/v10.4.1/

cleanconfopt=0 confopt=
var_append confopt ' ' --threads
var_append confopt ' ' --installprefix=$root/$prefix
